Phase 2 – Milestone 10: Agentforce AI

Activity 1: Enable Agentforce & AI Trust Settings
Objective: Enable Agentforce features securely and control AI access.

Steps
1. Go to Setup.
2. In the Quick Find box, search for Agentforce.
3. Click Agentforce Setup.
4. Click Enable Agentforce.
5. Go to AI Trust & Permissions.
6. Enable the following:
   • Data Masking
   • Zero Data Retention
   • Audit Logging
7. Assign Agentforce access to the following profiles:
   • System Administrator
   • Admissions Manager
8. Click Save.

---

Activity 2: Create Prompt Template – Student Application Summary
Objective: Generate an AI-based summary of a student enrollment for counselors and managers.

Steps
1. From Setup, search for Prompt Builder.
2. Click Prompt Builder.
3. Click New Prompt Template.
4. Select Prompt Type: Summary.
5. Select Object: Student_Enrollment__c.
6. Enter Prompt Name: Student Application Summary Prompt.
7. Enter the following prompt content:
Summarize the student application in simple terms including:
    • Student name
    • Course applied
    • Course fee and discount
    • Final payable amount
    • Enrollment status
    • AI priority score

Highlight any risks or special considerations.

8. Click Save.
9. Click Activate.

---

Activity 3: Create Prompt Template – Admission Risk Analysis
Objective: Help managers understand whether a student enrollment is risky or high value.

Steps
1. Go to Prompt Builder.
2. Click New Prompt Template.
3. Select Prompt Type: Flex.
4. Select Object: Student_Enrollment__c.
5. Enter Prompt Name: Student Enrollment Risk Analysis Prompt.
6. Enter the following prompt content:

Analyze this student enrollment and determine:

• Probability of successful admission
• Financial risk based on discount
• Overall enrollment health (Low, Medium, High Risk)

Provide recommendations for approval or rejection.

7. Click Save.
8. Click Activate.

---

Activity 4: Create Admissions AI Agent
Objective: Create an AI agent to assist counselors and managers during admissions.

Steps
1. From Setup, search for Agents.
2. Click Agents.
3. Click New Agent.
4. Enter the following details:
   Agent Name: Admissions Assistant Agent
   Description: AI agent to assist with student admissions and approvals.
5. Assign the following topics:
   • Student Application Summary
   • Enrollment Risk Analysis
   • Discount Approval Guidance
6. Click Next.

---

Activity 5: Configure Agent Actions
Objective: Allow the agent to take intelligent actions.

Steps
1. Open the Admissions Assistant Agent configuration.
2. Go to the Actions section.
3. Click Add Action.
4. Add the following actions:
   • Generate Student Application Summary
   • Analyze Enrollment Risk
   • Recommend Approval Decision
5. Map each action to the corresponding Prompt Template.
6. Click Save.

---

Activity 6: Configure Agent Data Library
Objective: Allow Agentforce to answer questions using Salesforce data.

Steps
1. Open the Admissions Assistant Agent.
2. Click Data Library.
3. Add the following objects:
   • Student__c
   • Course__c
   • Student_Enrollment__c
4. Set Access Level: Read Only.
5. Enable Field-Level Access Controls.
6. Click Save.

---

Activity 7: Test the Agent
Objective: Validate agent responses using real project data.

Steps
1. Open a Student Enrollment record.
2. Launch the Admissions Assistant Agent.
3. Ask the following questions:
   • "Summarize this student application."
   • "Is this enrollment safe to approve?"
   • "What risks are involved in this discount?"
4. Verify that the responses are accurate and relevant.

---

Activity 8: Deploy Agentforce
Objective: Make the agent available to users.

Steps
1. Go to Agent Deployment.
2. Choose Deployment Type: Lightning Experience.
3. Assign the deployment to:
   • Admissions Counselors
   • Admissions Managers
4. Click Deploy.
